 -- tFOREVER PANTING -- tJAMES THURBER: THE COMIC PRUFROCK -- tEXPLORING INNER SPACE0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aHarking from the golden age of fiction set in American suburbia—the school of John Updike and Cheever—this work from the great American humorist Peter De Vries looks with laughter upon its lawns, its cocktails, and its slightly unreal feeling of comfort. Without a Stitch in Time, a selection of forty-six articles and stories written for the New Yorker between 1943 and 1973, offers pun-filled autobiographical vignettes that reveal the source of De Vries’s nervous wit: the cognitive dissonance between his Calvinist upbringing in 1920s Chicago and the all-too-perfect postwar world. Noted as much for his verbal fluidity and wordplay as for his ability to see humor through pain, De Vries will delight both new readers and old in this uproarious modern masterpiece.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aShort stories, American. 0aWit and humor. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  ahumor, new yorker, fiction, vignettes, wordplay, suburbia, social commentary, mundane, puns, low comedy, calvinism, hypocrisy, human nature, foibles, jester, irony, wit, short stories, memoir, essays, nostalgia, postwar, striving, ambition, success, mobility, generations, absurdity, anthology, collection, publication, satire, middle class, white collar, office.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226171234423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226171234/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles